&lt;p&gt;Senior Care Assistant - Night Shifts&lt;br /&gt;Penylan House, Cardiff&lt;br /&gt;38.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;£11.10 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you enthusiastic with a real passion for Care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Want to work in a Senior Care Assistant role where you can make a real difference every day?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity for a committed and passionate Senior Care Assistant to join our team in our Penylan House Nursing Home, Cardiff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As the Senior Care Assistant, you will work closely with our Care Assistants and Nurses working as a supportive care team within an assigned &#39;community&#39; to deliver consistently high quality care, and we very much promote a team culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;d like to hear from you if you&#39;re a talented and experienced Carer, who understands care delivery and its pressures, and enjoys making a real difference to Elders&#39; lives. You&#39;ll need a minimum NVQ / QCF Level 2 in Health and Social Care and be committed to achieving an NVQ Level 3, along with previous experience of leading a staff team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be reliable and committed to making a positive difference to the Elders and have a genuine interest and enthusiasm in delivering person-centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be friendly with excellent communication skills and be able to manage multiple tasks through to completion and handle difficult situations sensitively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You&#39;ll need to adapt promptly to the changing needs of our Elders and always demonstrate sound judgement, common sense and initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don&#39;t delay - apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This advert closes at 23:45 on 22nd October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
